HEADWORD: Elul
<hw>E"lul</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.]</ety> <def>The
sixth month of the Jewish year, by the sacred reckoning, or the twelfth,
by the civil reckoning, corresponding nearly to the month of
September.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

